115
00:06:10.073 --> 00:06:11.700
Is that the footage from the scene?

116
00:06:11.783 --> 00:06:14.077
Yeah. Check it out.

117
00:06:14.161 --> 00:06:17.956
Turner takes two in the back.
and then the perp takes off.

118
00:06:17.998 --> 00:06:19.249
We lose him after that.

119
00:06:19.333 --> 00:06:20.959
Facial rec's no good.

120
00:06:21.043 --> 00:06:23.003
Perp's helmet and face
coverings saw to that.

121
00:06:23.028 --> 00:06:24.526
He knew what he was doing.

122
00:06:24.551 --> 00:06:26.482
So much so. I can't even
tell for sure if he's a he.

123
00:06:26.507 --> 00:06:27.674
Yeah.

124
00:06:27.758 --> 00:06:29.092
The shooter's bike is a Merrimac Pro.

125
00:06:29.176 --> 00:06:30.969
Second best-selling bike in New York.

126
00:06:31.094 --> 00:06:33.263
All right. well.
not a lot of help there.

127
00:06:33.305 --> 00:06:34.765
This might be.

128
00:06:34.848 --> 00:06:37.059
TARU got into Mark Turner's cloud.

129
00:06:37.142 --> 00:06:39.269
27 unanswered texts

130
00:06:39.394 --> 00:06:41.438
from a Bodie Walsh day of the murder.

131
00:06:41.522 --> 00:06:43.398
27 seems excessive.

132
00:06:43.524 --> 00:06:44.566
Wait till you read 'em.

133
00:06:44.691 --> 00:06:47.069
"How can you do this to me?

134
00:06:47.152 --> 00:06:48.695
There will be consequences."

135
00:06:48.737 --> 00:06:49.822
Right. Bodie Walsh is the head

136
00:06:49.905 --> 00:06:51.573
of an aviation consultant firm.

137
00:06:51.657 --> 00:06:54.284
SkyGuard Solutions. formed a month ago.

138
00:06:54.368 --> 00:06:56.453
His home in Astoria is
the corporate headquarters.

139
00:06:56.578 --> 00:06:59.373
One employee. the late Mark Turner.

140
00:06:59.456 --> 00:07:01.333
This last text from Bodie.

141
00:07:01.458 --> 00:07:04.878
"Arman Sargsyan doesn't mess around."

142
00:07:04.903 --> 00:07:05.954
If he says so.

143
00:07:05.979 --> 00:07:07.189
No. he's right.

144
00:07:07.214 --> 00:07:09.007
Sargsyan is a legit gangster.

145
00:07:09.091 --> 00:07:11.385
Loansharking. money laundering. drugs.

146
00:07:11.426 --> 00:07:13.095
How's a paper pusher like Mark Turner

147
00:07:13.178 --> 00:07:14.847
get involved with organized crime?

148
00:07:14.930 --> 00:07:17.266
Why don't you pay Mr. Walsh
a visit and find out?

149
00:07:20.853 --> 00:07:22.062
[BANGING]

150
00:07:22.187 --> 00:07:23.814
Bodie Walsh.

151
00:07:23.856 --> 00:07:25.440
NYPD. open up.

152
00:07:25.566 --> 00:07:26.942
Not a great time.

153
00:07:27.025 --> 00:07:28.674
What's this about?

154
00:07:29.403 --> 00:07:31.572
Murder investigation.

155
00:07:31.697 --> 00:07:33.907
[LOCKS CLICKING]

156
00:07:36.076 --> 00:07:38.203
Bodie Walsh?

157
00:07:38.245 --> 00:07:39.288
- That's me.
- Jesus.

158
00:07:39.413 --> 00:07:40.456
What happened to you?

159
00:07:40.481 --> 00:07:41.649
Can I help you?

160
00:07:41.674 --> 00:07:43.267
We need to talk about Mark Turner.

161
00:07:43.292 --> 00:07:46.211
[TENSE MUSIC]

162
00:07:46.253 --> 00:07:47.754
Can we go someplace?

163
00:07:47.838 --> 00:07:49.381
It doesn't feel safe here.

164
00:07:51.925 --> 00:07:53.302
Yeah. Yeah. get your stuff.

165
00:08:04.980 --> 00:08:06.982
Rough week?

166
00:08:09.234 --> 00:08:11.820
You wanna fill me in?

167
00:08:11.862 --> 00:08:14.573
Your face tells me
you owe the Armenians money.

168
00:08:16.492 --> 00:08:17.993
Was Mark Turner in the hole too?

169
00:08:18.118 --> 00:08:19.286
Is that why he's dead?

170
00:08:19.369 --> 00:08:20.471
God. no.

171
00:08:20.496 --> 00:08:21.580
Mark was a saint.

172
00:08:21.622 --> 00:08:22.998
Yeah. see. that's the point.

173
00:08:23.081 --> 00:08:25.042
As far as we can tell. you're not.

174
00:08:25.209 --> 00:08:26.502
You're in a bunch of debt.

175
00:08:26.543 --> 00:08:28.504
You owe money to some violent people.

176
00:08:28.545 --> 00:08:29.922
You threatened Mark with consequences.

177
00:08:30.005 --> 00:08:32.341
and now he's dead. I'm a murder cop.

178
00:08:32.424 --> 00:08:34.551
so you can see
where I'm going with this.

179
00:08:34.593 --> 00:08:36.261
I was in trouble.

180
00:08:36.303 --> 00:08:37.679
I needed Mark's help.

181
00:08:37.763 --> 00:08:40.182
That's why I wrote
those stupid messages.

182
00:08:40.224 --> 00:08:41.725
Explain.

183
00:08:41.850 --> 00:08:46.313
A lot of stuff I invested in
went belly up.

184
00:08:46.438 --> 00:08:48.982
and I doubled down and borrowed
money from the Armenians.

185
00:08:49.007 --> 00:08:50.137
And I don't have it.

186
00:08:50.162 --> 00:08:51.372
No kidding.

187
00:08:53.111 --> 00:08:54.530
Why Mark Turner?

188
00:08:54.655 --> 00:08:55.906
We grew up together.

189
00:08:56.031 --> 00:08:58.033
He went one way. I went the other.

190
00:08:58.116 --> 00:08:59.535
but we were gonna start a new business.

191
00:08:59.618 --> 00:09:01.829
Yeah. an aviation consulting firm.

192
00:09:01.870 --> 00:09:04.206
It was gonna work. too. I swear.

193
00:09:04.289 --> 00:09:07.376
See. guys like Mark. government guys.

194
00:09:07.501 --> 00:09:10.170
a lot of them go into
consulting when they retire.

195
00:09:10.212 --> 00:09:12.965
Well. it sounds ideal. What went wrong?

196
00:09:13.048 --> 00:09:15.676
I booked our first job.
and Mark wouldn't play ball.

197
00:09:15.701 --> 00:09:16.729
Why not?

198
00:09:16.754 --> 00:09:18.112
Job was with an insurance company.

199
00:09:18.137 --> 00:09:19.638
It was a skydiving accident.

200
00:09:19.680 --> 00:09:21.140
They didn't wanna pay up.

201
00:09:21.223 --> 00:09:24.268
Mark found out the person who
packed the parachute was uncertified.

202
00:09:24.393 --> 00:09:26.645
He didn't wanna let
the company off the hook.

203
00:09:26.728 --> 00:09:28.522
which was literally
what they were paying us to do.

204
00:09:28.547 --> 00:09:29.723
Yeah. And you needed the money.

205
00:09:29.748 --> 00:09:31.625
People have killed for less. Bodie.

206
00:09:31.650 --> 00:09:33.735
I didn't. I swear.

207
00:09:33.819 --> 00:09:35.779
Mark was too good for this world.

208
00:09:35.863 --> 00:09:38.073
He was such a goody two-shoes
about safety.

209
00:09:38.157 --> 00:09:39.950
People were always
getting pissed at him.

210
00:09:40.117 --> 00:09:41.451
He even got death threats.

211
00:09:41.535 --> 00:09:42.911
When?

212
00:09:42.995 --> 00:09:45.706
Like. the last few weeks.

213
00:09:45.831 --> 00:09:47.332
From who?

214
00:09:47.374 --> 00:09:49.251
A guy named Eric Savage.

215
00:09:49.334 --> 00:09:50.419
The boxer?

216
00:09:52.796 --> 00:09:54.214
[KNOCKS]

217
00:09:54.339 --> 00:09:55.674
Bodie's alibi checks out.

218
00:09:55.699 --> 00:09:56.823
Okay.

219
00:09:56.848 --> 00:09:58.527
He was right about those threats too.

220
00:09:58.552 --> 00:10:00.929
The warrant just dropped
for Turner's FAA cell.

221
00:10:00.971 --> 00:10:03.140
Eric Savage left
this voicemail last week.

222
00:10:03.223 --> 00:10:04.600
We checked the phone records
and everything.

223
00:10:04.683 --> 00:10:06.018
This is really him.

224
00:10:06.101 --> 00:10:08.979
Turner. you're a dead man. You hear me?

225
00:10:09.062 --> 00:10:11.982
What the hell is
mild-mannered Mark Turner doing

226
00:10:12.024 --> 00:10:14.651
tangled up with
a middleweight boxing champion?

227
00:10:14.776 --> 00:10:16.737
I mean. the dude's like Forrest Gump.

228
00:10:16.862 --> 00:10:19.364
Are you familiar with the Nomad Rocket?

229
00:10:19.490 --> 00:10:20.657
Space tourism for the rich and famous?

230
00:10:20.741 --> 00:10:21.867
Yeah.

231
00:10:21.950 --> 00:10:23.744
The FAA regulates
commercial space flight.

232
00:10:23.785 --> 00:10:25.913
Ten days ago. Mark Turner called off

233
00:10:25.996 --> 00:10:27.456
a launch at the last second.

234
00:10:27.581 --> 00:10:28.999
It caused quite a stir.

235
00:10:29.082 --> 00:10:30.876
Our boy Eric Savage was on that flight.

236
00:10:30.918 --> 00:10:32.002
Or he was supposed to be.

237
00:10:32.127 --> 00:10:33.587
He left that voicemail two days after

238
00:10:33.670 --> 00:10:35.172
Turner canceled the launch.

239
00:10:35.255 --> 00:10:36.965
And it turns out Eric Savage had

240
00:10:37.090 --> 00:10:39.301
a different career before boxing...

241
00:10:39.426 --> 00:10:42.513
aggravated assault. armed robbery.

242
00:10:42.638 --> 00:10:44.932
See what he has to say for himself.

243
00:10:51.355 --> 00:10:52.898
[GRUNTS]

244
00:10:52.981 --> 00:10:54.525
I'm gonna let you
take point on this one.

245
00:10:54.608 --> 00:10:55.692
Eric Savage.

246
00:10:55.776 --> 00:10:57.069
'Sup?

247
00:10:57.152 --> 00:10:58.403
Afternoon. guys.

248
00:10:58.487 --> 00:10:59.863
NYPD.

249
00:10:59.947 --> 00:11:01.114
[SIGHS]

250
00:11:01.156 --> 00:11:03.283
What can I do for New York's finest?

251
00:11:03.367 --> 00:11:06.453
Well. we have video of you

252
00:11:06.578 --> 00:11:09.213
walking into the lobby of
Mark Turner's office yesterday.

253
00:11:09.238 --> 00:11:10.245
And?

254
00:11:10.270 --> 00:11:13.377
And two hours later.
somebody shot him dead.

255
00:11:13.460 --> 00:11:14.670
Not a good look. man.

256
00:11:14.795 --> 00:11:16.213
I don't even own a gun.

257
00:11:16.296 --> 00:11:18.090
If I'm killing somebody.
I'm using my hands.

258
00:11:18.173 --> 00:11:20.092
Not exactly doing yourself
any favors there. Eric.

259
00:11:20.175 --> 00:11:22.886
We heard Turner crushed
your dreams of going to space.

260
00:11:22.970 --> 00:11:24.096
And that pissed you off. right?

261
00:11:24.179 --> 00:11:25.514
Yeah.

262
00:11:25.556 --> 00:11:27.599
Why should Katy Perry have all the fun?

263
00:11:27.641 --> 00:11:29.601
You know. I ask myself that
same question all the time.

264
00:11:29.685 --> 00:11:31.687
That flight would have got me triple

265
00:11:31.770 --> 00:11:33.313
the amount of Instagram followers.

266
00:11:33.355 --> 00:11:35.524
and it cost me a huge endorsement deal.

267
00:11:35.566 --> 00:11:37.526
So you threatened Mark Turner's life

268
00:11:37.609 --> 00:11:38.777
and then went down to his office

269
00:11:38.819 --> 00:11:40.070
to make good on those threats.

270
00:11:40.154 --> 00:11:41.405
I went to apologize.

271
00:11:41.530 --> 00:11:42.739
Really?

272
00:11:42.823 --> 00:11:44.533
Really.

273
00:11:44.616 --> 00:11:47.953
Look. man. Turner was right.

274
00:11:48.036 --> 00:11:49.621
I did my research.

275
00:11:49.663 --> 00:11:53.083
If we went up in the air.
my insides could have been vaporized.

276
00:11:53.167 --> 00:11:54.793
All right. let's say
we actually buy this story.

277
00:11:54.835 --> 00:11:56.170
How did Turner respond?

278
00:11:56.253 --> 00:11:57.963
He didn't.

279
00:11:58.005 --> 00:12:00.048
Security guard in the lobby
wouldn't even let me near him.

280
00:12:00.132 --> 00:12:02.217
Said there had been an incident.

281
00:12:02.301 --> 00:12:03.969
No outside visitors allowed.

282
00:12:05.304 --> 00:12:07.306
All right. we'll look into that.

283
00:12:11.018 --> 00:12:13.312
Do you remember this incident
that Eric Savage mentioned?

284
00:12:13.395 --> 00:12:14.897
Hard to forget.

285
00:12:14.938 --> 00:12:16.857
This crazy lady blew up
at a meeting upstairs.

286
00:12:16.982 --> 00:12:18.984
I had to pretty much drag her
out kicking and screaming.

287
00:12:19.026 --> 00:12:20.486
Who was she? You got a name?

288
00:12:20.511 --> 00:12:21.580
No idea.

289
00:12:21.605 --> 00:12:23.797
I was just told by brass
to escort her out.

290
00:12:23.822 --> 00:12:25.115
And when was this?

291
00:12:25.199 --> 00:12:27.993
Last Tuesday. right before
my shift ended. so about 5:00.

292
00:12:28.076 --> 00:12:29.620
All right. Thank you.

293
00:12:29.661 --> 00:12:30.913
Thank you.

294
00:12:30.996 --> 00:12:32.873
So according to Turner's calendar.

295
00:12:32.998 --> 00:12:35.918
that meeting was regarding
Titan Helicopter Corporation.

296
00:12:35.959 --> 00:12:39.135
Titan. That helicopter crash
out in Bayport last summer.

297
00:12:39.160 --> 00:12:41.315
Yeah. five people died.

298
00:12:41.340 --> 00:12:43.592
The pilot. a family of four.

299
00:12:43.717 --> 00:12:46.053
two kids. both under ten.

300
00:12:46.136 --> 00:12:48.387
That helicopter was a Titan.

301
00:12:48.722 --> 00:12:52.142
The day that bird went down
was the worst day of my life.

302
00:12:52.184 --> 00:12:54.186
That poor family.

303
00:12:54.269 --> 00:12:56.814
And what was this meeting
about at the FAA?

304
00:12:56.897 --> 00:12:58.649
Oh. standard practice.

305
00:12:58.690 --> 00:13:00.776
When the FAA completes an
investigation into an accident.

306
00:13:00.859 --> 00:13:02.653
they offer relevant parties

307
00:13:02.736 --> 00:13:04.905
a preview of their
official determination.

308
00:13:06.031 --> 00:13:07.574
Which was?

309
00:13:07.699 --> 00:13:09.243
Pilot error.

310
00:13:09.326 --> 00:13:10.452
Who was at this meeting?

311
00:13:10.577 --> 00:13:11.954
Mark Turner and a couple others

312
00:13:11.995 --> 00:13:14.832
from the FAA. a few of us from Titan.

313
00:13:14.915 --> 00:13:17.334
relatives of the deceased.
and Kate Leavy.

314
00:13:17.417 --> 00:13:19.002
wife of Brian Leavy. the pilot

315
00:13:19.128 --> 00:13:20.754
who was flying the day of the accident.

316
00:13:20.879 --> 00:13:23.132
What. she was the one
who freaked out at the meeting?

317
00:13:23.215 --> 00:13:24.716
Big time.

318
00:13:24.842 --> 00:13:27.177
Mark Turner headed up
that FAA investigation.

319
00:13:27.261 --> 00:13:29.138
which tells you it was done right.

320
00:13:29.304 --> 00:13:30.848
And Kate Leavy?

321
00:13:30.889 --> 00:13:33.976
Refused to accept that
pilot error caused the crash.

322
00:13:34.059 --> 00:13:35.561
It was ugly.

323
00:13:35.602 --> 00:13:37.312
She called Mark Turner a liar.

324
00:13:37.437 --> 00:13:40.315
said that her husband was ex-Marine.

325
00:13:40.399 --> 00:13:42.192
that they don't make errors.

326
00:13:42.276 --> 00:13:43.694
They had to haul her out of there.

327
00:13:43.777 --> 00:13:45.445
and she was screaming
into Turner's face.

328
00:13:45.529 --> 00:13:47.656
"This isn't over."

329
00:13:47.823 --> 00:13:49.533
[TENSE MUSIC]

330
00:13:49.616 --> 00:13:51.493
Yeah. I'm not exactly sure I buy

331
00:13:51.577 --> 00:13:53.537
Kate Leavy's a cold-blooded killer.

332
00:13:53.579 --> 00:13:55.247
She's got no priors.

333
00:13:55.372 --> 00:13:57.124
She teaches Sunday school
at Saint Catherine's.

334
00:13:57.291 --> 00:13:59.710
She posts on Instagram
about her hyacinths.

335
00:13:59.835 --> 00:14:02.963
Hey. turns out Kate Leavy's
husband. the helicopter pilot.

336
00:14:03.046 --> 00:14:04.756
owned a licensed Sig Sauer.

337
00:14:05.841 --> 00:14:08.844
There he is. Brian Leavy.

338
00:14:08.927 --> 00:14:10.345
And there's his firearm license.

339
00:14:10.429 --> 00:14:11.722
And according to forensics.

340
00:14:11.805 --> 00:14:13.891
the slugs removed
from Mark Turner's body had

341
00:14:13.974 --> 00:14:15.851
distinctive pin markings
indicating they were

342
00:14:15.976 --> 00:14:18.312
fired from a Sig Sauer.

343
00:14:18.353 --> 00:14:19.605
It's not enough for an arrest.

344
00:14:19.688 --> 00:14:21.565
It's enough for a chat.

345
00:14:21.648 --> 00:14:23.275
Okay.

346
00:14:25.444 --> 00:14:26.862
[BANGING]

347
00:14:26.945 --> 00:14:28.614
Kate Leavy. police.

348
00:14:30.699 --> 00:14:33.202
NYPD. Open up.

349
00:14:36.330 --> 00:14:37.331
NYPD.

350
00:14:37.456 --> 00:14:38.957
Oh. God.

351
00:14:39.041 --> 00:14:40.250
I don't know what to do.

352
00:14:40.334 --> 00:14:42.377
Yeah?

353
00:14:42.461 --> 00:14:44.213
Yeah. somebody's definitely home.

354
00:14:44.338 --> 00:14:47.716
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

355
00:14:47.758 --> 00:14:50.260
[KNOCKING]

356
00:14:50.385 --> 00:14:53.737
♪ ♪

357
00:15:09.029 --> 00:15:10.572
Hey. [WHISTLES SOFTLY]

358
00:15:10.614 --> 00:15:12.157
Gun. Go.

359
00:15:16.662 --> 00:15:19.915
Kate Leavy. NYPD.

360
00:15:23.168 --> 00:15:24.545
Kate Leavy.

361
00:15:29.675 --> 00:15:31.343
Hey.

362
00:15:31.426 --> 00:15:32.928
Drop that weapon. Kate.

363
00:15:34.847 --> 00:15:36.348
Drop that weapon.

364
00:15:43.480 --> 00:15:45.983
It's okay.

365
00:15:46.066 --> 00:15:49.278
Kate. take your hand off that gun.

366
00:15:52.156 --> 00:15:54.324
All right?

367
00:15:54.408 --> 00:15:56.076
Come on.

368
00:15:57.578 --> 00:16:00.456
Come on. I need you to
take your hand off the gun.

369
00:16:00.581 --> 00:16:03.292
Kate. stop right there.

370
00:16:03.333 --> 00:16:04.501
Okay? Hey.

371
00:16:04.543 --> 00:16:06.128
It's okay.

372
00:16:06.211 --> 00:16:07.379
Stay right where you are.

373
00:16:07.404 --> 00:16:08.488
Slowly.

374
00:16:08.513 --> 00:16:09.556
Keep your hands at your side.

375
00:16:09.581 --> 00:16:11.275
Keep your hands at your side. Kate.

376
00:16:11.300 --> 00:16:13.594
- Stay right there.
- It's okay.

377
00:16:13.635 --> 00:16:16.305
It's all right. Look at me. Face me.

378
00:16:16.388 --> 00:16:18.307
I'm gonna step to you. Okay?

379
00:16:18.390 --> 00:16:19.558
Here we go.

380
00:16:21.602 --> 00:16:23.103
I got it. I got it.

381
00:16:23.145 --> 00:16:24.646
- [SHOUTS]
- Okay. You're okay.

382
00:16:24.730 --> 00:16:26.732
Turn around.

383
00:16:26.815 --> 00:16:28.025
Please. please. please.

384
00:16:28.066 --> 00:16:29.401
Please. please!

385
00:16:29.485 --> 00:16:30.861
Easy.

386
00:16:30.986 --> 00:16:33.113
Kate?

387
00:16:33.238 --> 00:16:34.239
What's happening?

388
00:16:34.281 --> 00:16:35.616
Is everything okay?

389
00:16:35.741 --> 00:16:37.201
Who else is in this house?

390
00:16:37.326 --> 00:16:38.744
No one.

391
00:16:38.869 --> 00:16:40.579
Don't lie to me.
How many people are in here?

392
00:16:40.704 --> 00:16:42.456
Talk to me. Kate. Say something.

393
00:16:42.581 --> 00:16:43.582
Anything.

394
00:16:43.665 --> 00:16:44.917
You're really scaring me now.

395
00:16:44.958 --> 00:16:47.419
Sir. I'm coming toward you.
I have a weapon.

396
00:16:47.503 --> 00:16:49.588
- Are you armed?
- What? No.

397
00:16:49.671 --> 00:16:51.757
Kate. what is happening? Are you okay?

398
00:16:51.799 --> 00:16:53.467
Please tell me you're okay.

399
00:16:53.550 --> 00:16:54.760
It's the police.

400
00:16:54.843 --> 00:16:55.969
I'm okay.

401
00:16:55.994 --> 00:16:58.138
The police? Oh. my God.
Please don't hurt her.

402
00:16:58.163 --> 00:16:59.448
Sir. I'm stepping inside.

403
00:16:59.473 --> 00:17:01.433
My weapon is drawn.
and I will shoot you.

404
00:17:01.458 --> 00:17:02.876
Raise your hands and keep them
where I can see them.

405
00:17:03.018 --> 00:17:04.436
Do you understand?

406
00:17:04.520 --> 00:17:09.107
♪ ♪

407
00:17:09.149 --> 00:17:12.499
Please be gentle with her.

408
00:17:12.524 --> 00:17:13.622
Who the hell are you?

409
00:17:13.647 --> 00:17:14.780
I'm Brian.

410
00:17:14.822 --> 00:17:17.783
Brian Leavy. Kate's husband.

411
00:17:17.866 --> 00:17:22.412
But you died in a helicopter
crash two months ago.

412
00:17:22.538 --> 00:17:27.000
♪ ♪

413
00:17:32.092 --> 00:17:34.140
I haven't seen you in
those earrings in a while.

414
00:17:34.165 --> 00:17:36.626
Oh. yeah.

415
00:17:37.261 --> 00:17:38.804
Remember when you got them for me

416
00:17:38.846 --> 00:17:40.472
at that place up in Ithaca?

417
00:17:40.597 --> 00:17:42.933
Oh. my God. remember that place?

418
00:17:42.975 --> 00:17:44.226
[LAUGHS] Oh.

419
00:17:44.351 --> 00:17:45.727
That guy who rented it to us?

420
00:17:45.811 --> 00:17:48.147
Kate Leavy is not talking.

421
00:17:48.188 --> 00:17:51.567
The only hard evidence we have
is the murder weapon. maybe.

422
00:17:51.608 --> 00:17:53.694
And forensics won't be back
for 48 hours.

423
00:17:53.819 --> 00:17:55.946
We can only hold her for 42.

424
00:17:55.988 --> 00:17:57.322
What have we got?

425
00:17:57.347 --> 00:17:58.682
We just got the warrant for her devices.

426
00:17:58.707 --> 00:18:01.377
but it turns out
Theo didn't see a ghost there.

427
00:18:01.702 --> 00:18:04.538
Say hello to the late Brian Leavy.

428
00:18:04.580 --> 00:18:05.664
This place has rustic charm.

429
00:18:05.747 --> 00:18:09.126
And here I was thinking
death was a fairly permanent condition.

430
00:18:09.168 --> 00:18:10.461
Used to be. right?

431
00:18:10.544 --> 00:18:12.254
This Brian Leavy is
known as a grief bot.

432
00:18:12.337 --> 00:18:14.131
He's a hyper-realistic. AI-powered

433
00:18:14.256 --> 00:18:15.799
simulation of a dead guy.

434
00:18:15.841 --> 00:18:18.177
After he died. Kate Leavy got
a subscription to a thing

435
00:18:18.302 --> 00:18:21.096
called Memory Branch... $49.99 a month.

436
00:18:21.180 --> 00:18:22.848
She talks to her husband all the time.

437
00:18:22.973 --> 00:18:25.726
There's. like. 500 hours of recorded
conversations between these two.

438
00:18:25.751 --> 00:18:27.502
They talk about what
they want for dinner.

439
00:18:27.769 --> 00:18:29.021
They talk about movies they've seen.

440
00:18:29.062 --> 00:18:30.731
That sounds terrible.

441
00:18:30.814 --> 00:18:33.233
I mean. kinda. but I don't know.

442
00:18:33.275 --> 00:18:34.776
Part of me also gets it. you know?

443
00:18:34.902 --> 00:18:35.986
My brother's in a coma.

444
00:18:36.111 --> 00:18:37.529
If I could talk to an avatar of him

445
00:18:37.654 --> 00:18:39.907
about. you know.
the Yankees or something.

446
00:18:39.948 --> 00:18:41.450
I don't know. maybe that would help.

447
00:18:43.452 --> 00:18:44.703
How are we supposed to get through

448
00:18:44.828 --> 00:18:47.039
500 hours of this in the next 42 hours?

449
00:18:47.122 --> 00:18:48.499
We might not need to.

450
00:18:48.540 --> 00:18:51.293
I've been working my way
backwards from the murder.

451
00:18:51.376 --> 00:18:52.753
Kate. these people are trying

452
00:18:52.836 --> 00:18:54.213
to destroy my reputation.

453
00:18:54.254 --> 00:18:55.881
I did nothing wrong.

454
00:18:55.923 --> 00:18:58.467
That helicopter was doomed.

455
00:18:58.509 --> 00:19:01.970
If it weren't for them.
I'd still be alive.

456
00:19:02.095 --> 00:19:05.599
I can't fight back.

457
00:19:05.724 --> 00:19:08.101
but you can.

458
00:19:08.185 --> 00:19:12.648
What does this thing know.

459
00:19:12.731 --> 00:19:14.316
like. about the real world?

460
00:19:14.358 --> 00:19:15.859
I mean. is there any truth
to any of this?

461
00:19:15.901 --> 00:19:17.027
We don't know yet.

462
00:19:17.069 --> 00:19:18.529
Run it down.

463
00:19:18.570 --> 00:19:20.322
I mean. if dead Brian Leavy's
telling the truth.

464
00:19:20.364 --> 00:19:23.492
then we're talking
about motive... revenge.

465
00:19:23.617 --> 00:19:27.412
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

466
00:19:27.538 --> 00:19:31.583
Look. I want answers here
as much as you do.

467
00:19:31.708 --> 00:19:33.919
Everybody here thought
the world of Mark Turner.

468
00:19:34.086 --> 00:19:36.088
That's not the question. is it?

469
00:19:36.213 --> 00:19:37.631
We found those in a trove of documents

470
00:19:37.714 --> 00:19:39.883
that Titan handed over
when the FAA investigated

471
00:19:40.008 --> 00:19:41.635
the crash on Long Island.

472
00:19:41.718 --> 00:19:43.679
It says the tail rotor
that was used on the helicopter

473
00:19:43.762 --> 00:19:45.806
had been dinged
in a previous inspection.

474
00:19:45.889 --> 00:19:47.391
Was that tail rotor still on
the helicopter when it crashed?

475
00:19:47.474 --> 00:19:48.522
No.

476
00:19:48.547 --> 00:19:50.508
Is there some kind
of cover-up going on here?

477
00:19:50.936 --> 00:19:52.146
Was Mark Turner crooked?

478
00:19:52.312 --> 00:19:53.981
Would somebody pay him off
to pin this all

479
00:19:54.006 --> 00:19:55.193
on Brian Leavy. a dead guy?

480
00:19:55.218 --> 00:19:57.512
No. For God's sake. no.

481
00:19:58.902 --> 00:20:00.237
It's true.

482
00:20:00.362 --> 00:20:01.989
The helicopter that crashed
once used a rotor

483
00:20:02.030 --> 00:20:03.657
- that had some bearing wear.
- Uh-huh.

484
00:20:03.699 --> 00:20:05.576
Basically. the rotor and drive shaft

485
00:20:05.659 --> 00:20:08.245
were misaligned.
but that's not why it crashed.

486
00:20:08.370 --> 00:20:10.789
♪ ♪

487
00:20:10.873 --> 00:20:12.207
What is this?

488
00:20:12.332 --> 00:20:14.460
Titan swapped out
that wonky rotor for a new one

489
00:20:14.501 --> 00:20:16.628
a month before the crash.

490
00:20:16.712 --> 00:20:18.630
We've got video of them doing
the work in their hangar.

491
00:20:18.714 --> 00:20:20.257
You're welcome to see it.

492
00:20:20.424 --> 00:20:24.636
It brings me no joy to tell you
this was textbook pilot error.

493
00:20:24.720 --> 00:20:29.308
♪ ♪

494
00:20:29.391 --> 00:20:32.060
We're testing the gun
that we seized at your home

495
00:20:32.186 --> 00:20:36.398
to confirm it's the gun that
was used to kill Mark Turner.

496
00:20:36.482 --> 00:20:39.902
But we already know the answer.
don't we?

497
00:20:46.241 --> 00:20:49.453
A friend of mine was killed
a couple of months ago.

498
00:20:49.536 --> 00:20:50.871
He was a cop.

499
00:20:52.831 --> 00:20:54.082
I'm sorry.

500
00:20:54.124 --> 00:20:56.919
I didn't know Walker knew that guy.

501
00:20:56.960 --> 00:20:58.462
No.

502
00:20:58.587 --> 00:21:00.297
No. he doesn't. He's making this up.

503
00:21:00.380 --> 00:21:02.341
This is what he does.
He's a storyteller.

504
00:21:02.424 --> 00:21:05.052
I'm still fighting through it.

505
00:21:05.093 --> 00:21:06.720
You know the part I can't shake?

506
00:21:06.845 --> 00:21:09.223
It's not being sad.

507
00:21:09.306 --> 00:21:11.391
I can handle that.

508
00:21:11.517 --> 00:21:14.186
I'm angry. Kate.

509
00:21:14.269 --> 00:21:18.774
angry at my dead friend
and myself and God.

510
00:21:18.899 --> 00:21:20.776
And I think you're angry too.

511
00:21:23.195 --> 00:21:25.656
It hurts.

512
00:21:25.697 --> 00:21:26.732
It's not fair.

513
00:21:26.757 --> 00:21:28.408
It's not.

514
00:21:28.450 --> 00:21:30.828
I read this thing the other day

515
00:21:30.953 --> 00:21:33.664
that said grief is
just another form of love.

516
00:21:33.747 --> 00:21:37.000
love that's got no place to go.

517
00:21:37.084 --> 00:21:39.962
And there was a lot of love. right?

518
00:21:40.087 --> 00:21:42.422
Your husband was a great man.

519
00:21:42.447 --> 00:21:45.585
But the reality is. he made a mistake.

520
00:21:45.610 --> 00:21:46.802
No.

521
00:21:46.844 --> 00:21:48.720
Yes.

522
00:21:48.762 --> 00:21:51.598
I know he told you there was
a bad part on the helicopter.

523
00:21:51.682 --> 00:21:54.685
We've seen the recordings
of your conversation.

524
00:21:54.726 --> 00:21:58.939
But your husband is only privy
to what's on the internet.

525
00:21:58.981 --> 00:22:01.150
because he's a computer program. Kate.

526
00:22:08.031 --> 00:22:09.658
Yes.

527
00:22:09.741 --> 00:22:12.161
This is what Brian showed me. the rotor.

528
00:22:12.244 --> 00:22:13.579
He found it online because it's part of

529
00:22:13.662 --> 00:22:16.748
the public records connected
to the FAA investigation.

530
00:22:19.084 --> 00:22:22.796
But he didn't know about this...

531
00:22:25.716 --> 00:22:27.843
Because the FAA's
internal work documents

532
00:22:27.885 --> 00:22:30.637
are not part of the public record yet.

533
00:22:30.721 --> 00:22:31.930
That rotor got changed out.

534
00:22:32.055 --> 00:22:33.682
There was nothing wrong
with that helicopter.

535
00:22:33.807 --> 00:22:36.560
[SOFT SOMBER MUSIC]

536
00:22:36.685 --> 00:22:39.062
♪ ♪

537
00:22:39.146 --> 00:22:41.690
You will know the truth.

538
00:22:41.773 --> 00:22:43.817
and the truth will set you free.

539
00:22:45.235 --> 00:22:46.737
John 8:32.

540
00:22:46.778 --> 00:22:49.114
That's right.

541
00:22:49.198 --> 00:22:50.699
Pray with me?

542
00:22:53.324 --> 00:22:55.179
We don't really do
that kind of thing in here.

543
00:22:55.204 --> 00:22:57.790
Please.

544
00:22:57.915 --> 00:23:02.252
I can see that you want to pray with me.

545
00:23:02.377 --> 00:23:04.968
♪ ♪

546
00:23:11.553 --> 00:23:14.030
Heavenly father.

547
00:23:14.055 --> 00:23:18.118
bless this man. your servant.

548
00:23:18.143 --> 00:23:20.229
who seeks the truth.

549
00:23:23.023 --> 00:23:25.901
And forgive me for what I've done.

550
00:23:28.237 --> 00:23:29.404
Okay.

551
00:23:31.339 --> 00:23:34.635
I practiced for a few days
riding my bike with one hand

552
00:23:34.660 --> 00:23:37.454
so I'd be ready to shoot
my gun with the other.

553
00:23:37.579 --> 00:23:38.956
And on the day it happened.

554
00:23:39.039 --> 00:23:41.291
did you follow Mark Turner
from his office?

555
00:23:41.375 --> 00:23:42.709
No.

556
00:23:42.835 --> 00:23:45.129
I memorized his schedule.

557
00:23:45.170 --> 00:23:48.924
I knew when he left work.
how he rode home each day.

558
00:23:49.049 --> 00:23:50.801
so I knew where he'd be.

559
00:23:50.884 --> 00:23:55.343
I waited. and there he was.

560
00:23:56.014 --> 00:23:58.058
It was so fast.

561
00:23:58.183 --> 00:24:01.562
I rode up behind him
and shot him in the back.

562
00:24:01.603 --> 00:24:04.439
It's textbook premeditated murder.

563
00:24:04.523 --> 00:24:06.942
Sometimes they come with a bow on top.

564
00:24:06.984 --> 00:24:08.026
[KNOCKING]

565
00:24:08.193 --> 00:24:10.529
Sig Sauer handgun we recovered

566
00:24:10.554 --> 00:24:13.223
from Kate Leavy's home
is not the murder weapon.

567
00:24:13.248 --> 00:24:14.341
That's weird.

568
00:24:14.366 --> 00:24:15.576
Maybe not.

569
00:24:15.617 --> 00:24:16.869
About a week before the murder.

570
00:24:16.994 --> 00:24:20.664
she went online
and got herself a barrel kit.

571
00:24:20.747 --> 00:24:22.416
She swapped out
the barrel of the Sig Sauer

572
00:24:22.499 --> 00:24:24.168
so when forensics tested the gun...

573
00:24:24.293 --> 00:24:26.378
The marks on the test slugs
were different

574
00:24:26.403 --> 00:24:28.613
from the slugs we pulled
from Mark Turner's body.

575
00:24:28.755 --> 00:24:30.424
We'd certainly be in a stronger position

576
00:24:30.507 --> 00:24:31.967
if we had the murder weapon.

577
00:24:32.009 --> 00:24:33.385
but this is pretty
compelling evidence that

578
00:24:33.427 --> 00:24:35.971
she tried to cover her tracks.

579
00:24:36.054 --> 00:24:37.598
We'll still need to get ahead of this.

580
00:24:37.639 --> 00:24:39.391
The defense will make a meal of it.

581
00:24:39.516 --> 00:24:41.643
But in the meantime.
Kate Leavy confessed

582
00:24:41.727 --> 00:24:43.979
she shot Mark Turner with a gun.

583
00:24:44.062 --> 00:24:46.038
A confession's a confession.

584
00:24:48.942 --> 00:24:51.069
Your Honor. Detective Walker's decision

585
00:24:51.195 --> 00:24:53.363
to join hands and pray with Kate Leavy

586
00:24:53.489 --> 00:24:55.199
while she was in police custody

587
00:24:55.282 --> 00:24:57.367
is clearly grounds
to quash this confession.

588
00:24:57.493 --> 00:24:58.869
That is not true. Your Honor.

589
00:24:58.952 --> 00:25:00.746
I mean. that prayer may
have been unusual.

590
00:25:00.788 --> 00:25:02.155
but it's not illegal.

591
00:25:02.180 --> 00:25:04.224
And it was Kate Leavy who asked to pray

592
00:25:04.249 --> 00:25:06.518
with Detective Walker.
not the other way around.

593
00:25:06.543 --> 00:25:08.212
But that doesn't matter. Your Honor.

594
00:25:08.295 --> 00:25:10.714
This goes back
to Miranda case law itself.

595
00:25:10.798 --> 00:25:13.300
Confessions must be voluntary.

596
00:25:13.342 --> 00:25:15.844
And it was. and there was no threat.

597
00:25:15.969 --> 00:25:17.763
no... no promise. no inducement.

598
00:25:17.846 --> 00:25:21.517
Which is immaterial as well.
because prayer all on its own

599
00:25:21.642 --> 00:25:23.727
has been seen by the courts routinely

600
00:25:23.769 --> 00:25:26.480
as a form of psychological
coercion by the police.

601
00:25:26.522 --> 00:25:29.650
Coercion renders
a confession involuntary

602
00:25:29.733 --> 00:25:31.902
and therefore inadmissible.

603
00:25:31.927 --> 00:25:33.304
- Your Honor...
- Save your breath. Mr. Price.

604
00:25:33.329 --> 00:25:35.739
I agree with Ms. Hogan.
The confession is out.

605
00:25:35.781 --> 00:25:38.200
[TENSE MUSIC]

606
00:25:43.403 --> 00:25:45.933
We're still good on motive.

607
00:25:45.958 --> 00:25:49.670
I've watched hours of Kate Leavy's
conversations with her "husband."

608
00:25:49.795 --> 00:25:52.131
I mean. if I'm being honest.
I can't stop watching them.

609
00:25:52.214 --> 00:25:53.340
It's unsettling.

610
00:25:53.423 --> 00:25:55.384
It's creepy is what it is.

611
00:25:55.425 --> 00:25:57.594
She was consumed by her husband's death.

612
00:25:57.636 --> 00:25:59.763
craved retribution.

613
00:25:59.847 --> 00:26:01.473
The more technology tries to help.

614
00:26:01.515 --> 00:26:02.808
the worse things seem to get.

615
00:26:02.891 --> 00:26:05.102
Everything has a shortcut these days.

616
00:26:05.144 --> 00:26:07.271
Overweight? Try Ozempic.

617
00:26:07.312 --> 00:26:09.064
Lonely? Swipe right.

618
00:26:09.106 --> 00:26:10.607
Can't handle the death of a loved one?

619
00:26:10.649 --> 00:26:12.317
Create a grief bot.

620
00:26:12.359 --> 00:26:13.986
Grief is supposed to be hard.

621
00:26:14.027 --> 00:26:15.779
Pretty sure that's the point.

622
00:26:15.863 --> 00:26:17.906
If you can believe it.
I've got a voicemail

623
00:26:17.990 --> 00:26:19.616
from my father that he left

624
00:26:19.741 --> 00:26:21.493
a couple of days before he died.

625
00:26:21.618 --> 00:26:23.912
which. for all I know.
he was trying to get me

626
00:26:23.954 --> 00:26:26.790
to smuggle scotch
into the hospital. but...

627
00:26:26.832 --> 00:26:28.500
I can't even listen.

628
00:26:28.584 --> 00:26:31.628
Grief is obviously
a universal experience.

629
00:26:31.712 --> 00:26:33.297
which means everyone on that jury

630
00:26:33.380 --> 00:26:35.174
has experienced it in some capacity.

631
00:26:35.257 --> 00:26:39.970
So lean into the anger
and confusion of that journey.

632
00:26:40.095 --> 00:26:42.097
That's what drove Kate Leavy to kill.

633
00:26:46.143 --> 00:26:48.103
Ms. Leavy's cell phone
pinged off a tower

634
00:26:48.228 --> 00:26:50.898
on West 61st Street at 6:12 p.m..

635
00:26:51.023 --> 00:26:53.734
putting her roughly within
150 yards of the murder.

636
00:26:53.859 --> 00:26:56.945
Can you explain these images.
Detective Walker?

637
00:26:56.987 --> 00:26:59.490
On the left is an image
from security footage.

638
00:26:59.573 --> 00:27:03.285
the killer on
a 2023 Merrimac Pro bicycle.

639
00:27:03.327 --> 00:27:05.913
On the right is that same
make and model bicycle

640
00:27:06.038 --> 00:27:08.207
recovered from the basement
of Ms. Leavy's home.

641
00:27:08.290 --> 00:27:10.876
Lastly. Detective. when
you went to Ms. Leavy's home

642
00:27:10.959 --> 00:27:14.254
to question her. how would you
describe her demeanor?

643
00:27:14.338 --> 00:27:16.173
Rattled.

644
00:27:16.215 --> 00:27:18.425
Panicked. maybe.

645
00:27:18.509 --> 00:27:20.844
When we arrived. we knocked.

646
00:27:20.928 --> 00:27:22.638
We announced ourselves
as police several times.

647
00:27:22.721 --> 00:27:24.598
but she refused to open up.

648
00:27:24.681 --> 00:27:27.351
We went inside because we were
concerned for her safety.

649
00:27:27.434 --> 00:27:29.895
We could see her pacing frantically.

650
00:27:29.937 --> 00:27:31.563
She had a firearm next to her.

651
00:27:31.605 --> 00:27:32.648
Nothing further. Your Honor.

652
00:27:32.731 --> 00:27:34.691
Ms. Hogan.

653
00:27:34.775 --> 00:27:37.069
Detective. how many other phones

654
00:27:37.236 --> 00:27:39.238
pinged off of that cell phone tower

655
00:27:39.279 --> 00:27:40.864
around the time of the murder?

656
00:27:40.906 --> 00:27:43.200
About 3.000.

657
00:27:43.325 --> 00:27:45.701
So what you're saying is

658
00:27:45.726 --> 00:27:48.997
2.999 other people

659
00:27:49.081 --> 00:27:50.666
could have committed this murder.

660
00:27:50.749 --> 00:27:52.251
Respectfully. we're here because

661
00:27:52.334 --> 00:27:54.086
we believe the defendant
committed this murder.

662
00:27:54.169 --> 00:27:56.213
The gravest allegation one can face.

663
00:27:56.296 --> 00:27:59.091
So. surely. you cleared
those other people

664
00:27:59.216 --> 00:28:01.635
by interviewing them. obtaining alibis.

665
00:28:01.677 --> 00:28:03.011
We didn't think that was necessary.

666
00:28:03.137 --> 00:28:05.180
I'm sure you didn't.

667
00:28:05.264 --> 00:28:09.309
Now. based on this image.
it's impossible to know

668
00:28:09.351 --> 00:28:11.770
if the killer was a man or a woman.

669
00:28:11.854 --> 00:28:12.938
[TENSE MUSIC]

670
00:28:12.980 --> 00:28:15.232
Based on that image. maybe.

671
00:28:15.399 --> 00:28:16.608
But we have more evidence.

672
00:28:16.633 --> 00:28:18.260
Have police ever banged on your door?

673
00:28:19.570 --> 00:28:20.654
No.

674
00:28:20.737 --> 00:28:21.947
But if they did.

675
00:28:22.114 --> 00:28:24.199
it would make you frantic. correct?

676
00:28:25.534 --> 00:28:27.435
Especially if you were innocent.

677
00:28:29.692 --> 00:28:30.943
One last thing.

678
00:28:30.968 --> 00:28:33.267
There were 6.000 Merrimac Pro bicycles

679
00:28:33.292 --> 00:28:35.127
sold in 2023.

680
00:28:35.169 --> 00:28:38.255
Surely. you interviewed these
people who own these bikes.

681
00:28:38.338 --> 00:28:39.673
That wasn't necessary.

682
00:28:39.840 --> 00:28:42.092
You had your suspect. so damn the facts.

683
00:28:42.176 --> 00:28:43.677
Objection. Your Honor.

684
00:28:43.802 --> 00:28:45.345
Sustained.

685
00:28:45.429 --> 00:28:46.472
Nothing else. Your Honor.

686
00:28:49.732 --> 00:28:52.811
A gun barrel imparts marks
on the projectile that fires.

687
00:28:52.895 --> 00:28:56.273
marks that we in the ballistics
field call lands and grooves.

688
00:28:56.398 --> 00:28:58.567
They are specific to that firearm.

689
00:28:58.692 --> 00:29:01.778
kind of like how fingerprints
are specific to each of us.

690
00:29:01.862 --> 00:29:03.822
And a firearm can be taken apart

691
00:29:03.864 --> 00:29:06.408
and put back together again.
including the barrel. correct?

692
00:29:06.450 --> 00:29:10.078
Yes.
It's common among firearm enthusiasts.

693
00:29:10.162 --> 00:29:13.248
You can buy barrel kits
to swap out that piece.

694
00:29:13.332 --> 00:29:16.335
And then those markings.
those lands and grooves?

695
00:29:16.376 --> 00:29:17.961
Would be new. different.

696
00:29:18.003 --> 00:29:21.173
Which would explain how
a weapon could be used to kill.

697
00:29:21.215 --> 00:29:24.551
but a forensics investigation
would conclude that it wasn't.

698
00:29:24.635 --> 00:29:25.844
Correct.

699
00:29:25.928 --> 00:29:27.429
Nothing further.

700
00:29:29.932 --> 00:29:32.601
Kate Leavy was never found
in possession of the gun barrel

701
00:29:32.726 --> 00:29:34.728
that was used in this murder.

702
00:29:34.812 --> 00:29:38.142
So this theory that Ms. Leavy.

703
00:29:38.166 --> 00:29:40.609
a literal Sunday school teacher

704
00:29:40.651 --> 00:29:42.820
without so much as a jaywalking ticket.

705
00:29:42.903 --> 00:29:46.073
is such a criminal mastermind
that she swapped out

706
00:29:46.198 --> 00:29:49.201
these gun barrels to cover
her tracks is just that...

707
00:29:49.226 --> 00:29:50.469
a theory. correct?

708
00:29:50.494 --> 00:29:52.412
Objection. Counsel is testifying.

709
00:29:52.437 --> 00:29:53.529
Sustained.

710
00:29:53.554 --> 00:29:56.016
It's impossible to determine
whether the gun found

711
00:29:56.041 --> 00:29:58.919
in Ms. Leavy's apartment was the gun
used to kill Mark Turner.

712
00:29:58.944 --> 00:30:00.229
- Correct?
- Correct.

713
00:30:00.254 --> 00:30:01.296
But the barrel she purchased...

714
00:30:01.380 --> 00:30:02.881
Nothing else. Your Honor.

715
00:30:07.052 --> 00:30:10.389
Grief is more than missing someone.

716
00:30:10.430 --> 00:30:14.726
The loss of a parent. a spouse.
a child. it's so powerful.

717
00:30:14.810 --> 00:30:18.355
it can disrupt our very sense
of meaning. identity.

718
00:30:18.480 --> 00:30:21.900
Recovery means rebuilding our story.

719
00:30:22.025 --> 00:30:24.653
incorporating that loss
into a new narrative.

720
00:30:24.678 --> 00:30:26.513
And these grief bots?

721
00:30:26.538 --> 00:30:29.874
At Memory Branch. we refer
to them as legacy avatars.

722
00:30:29.899 --> 00:30:31.442
Forgive me.

723
00:30:31.467 --> 00:30:33.848
These legacy avatars help
those who are mourning

724
00:30:33.873 --> 00:30:34.930
do all of that?

725
00:30:34.955 --> 00:30:36.123
Yes.

726
00:30:36.165 --> 00:30:39.209
Articulate memories. clarify emotions.

727
00:30:39.334 --> 00:30:41.587
say the stuff that was left unsaid.

728
00:30:41.628 --> 00:30:43.589
It's a form of therapy.

729
00:30:43.630 --> 00:30:46.216
It's not quite that simple.
though. is it. Ms. Matthews?

730
00:30:46.300 --> 00:30:50.512
Kate Leavy paid your company
$49.99 a month

731
00:30:50.596 --> 00:30:52.890
to speak with her deceased husband.

732
00:30:52.973 --> 00:30:55.225
- Yes.
- But if she woke up one day

733
00:30:55.309 --> 00:30:58.312
and decided that she was cured
of her grief.

734
00:30:58.437 --> 00:31:00.772
she might discontinue
her subscription. correct?

735
00:31:00.814 --> 00:31:02.357
Yes. Some people do.

736
00:31:02.399 --> 00:31:04.401
Which means your
revenue stream is maximized

737
00:31:04.485 --> 00:31:06.320
by keeping your clients.

738
00:31:06.403 --> 00:31:10.449
people who are mourning. hooked.

739
00:31:10.491 --> 00:31:12.826
I wouldn't put it that way.

740
00:31:12.951 --> 00:31:17.247
Your company programs
legacy avatars like Brian Leavy

741
00:31:17.331 --> 00:31:19.958
to be echo chambers. correct?

742
00:31:20.083 --> 00:31:22.503
Isn't it true that
they are built specifically

743
00:31:22.669 --> 00:31:25.214
to amplify whatever
sentiment is expressed

744
00:31:25.339 --> 00:31:26.799
by your grieving clients?

745
00:31:26.840 --> 00:31:28.425
Yes. basically. the client...

746
00:31:28.467 --> 00:31:31.136
So then wasn't it true
that when Kate Leavy insisted

747
00:31:31.178 --> 00:31:35.808
to her husband that someone
must be to blame for his death.

748
00:31:35.849 --> 00:31:37.601
he was happy to oblige?

749
00:31:37.643 --> 00:31:42.439
Your legacy avatar eagerly
coughed up a cockamamie story

750
00:31:42.464 --> 00:31:43.840
about a sinister cover-up.

751
00:31:43.865 --> 00:31:45.518
Objection. Leading.

752
00:31:45.543 --> 00:31:46.627
Sustained.

753
00:31:46.652 --> 00:31:49.154
He was trying to help her.

754
00:31:49.238 --> 00:31:51.990
♪ ♪

755
00:31:52.032 --> 00:31:54.409
Your Honor. the people would
like to introduce the video

756
00:31:54.493 --> 00:31:56.578
of the relevant conversations
between Kate Leavy

757
00:31:56.703 --> 00:31:58.372
and Brian Leavy's avatar.

758
00:31:58.413 --> 00:32:00.415
what has been marked as exhibit 11A.

759
00:32:00.457 --> 00:32:02.835
We object to the introduction
of that video

760
00:32:02.918 --> 00:32:04.962
and any other recordings
of conversations

761
00:32:05.087 --> 00:32:07.172
between my client and her husband.

762
00:32:07.256 --> 00:32:08.966
On what grounds?

763
00:32:09.007 --> 00:32:11.343
These videos are protected
by marital privilege.

764
00:32:11.385 --> 00:32:12.803
You cannot be serious.

765
00:32:12.886 --> 00:32:15.097
Chambers. now.

766
00:32:18.392 --> 00:32:21.812
Your Honor. this avatar
is not Brian Leavy.

767
00:32:21.837 --> 00:32:23.589
It's a computer program.

768
00:32:23.614 --> 00:32:26.375
Communications between
the defendant and this thing

769
00:32:26.400 --> 00:32:27.776
is clearly fair game.

770
00:32:27.818 --> 00:32:30.404
Your Honor. it is true
that this legacy avatar

771
00:32:30.445 --> 00:32:33.198
is powered by AI. but he possesses

772
00:32:33.282 --> 00:32:35.409
and has mastered the real Brian Leavy's

773
00:32:35.492 --> 00:32:37.494
entire digital footprint...

774
00:32:37.578 --> 00:32:41.498
Brian Leavy's likeness.
voice. mannerisms.

775
00:32:41.582 --> 00:32:46.336
every social media post.
his past. his life.

776
00:32:46.462 --> 00:32:48.547
When Kate Leavy interacted with him.

777
00:32:48.672 --> 00:32:51.049
she firmly believed she was
speaking with her husband.

778
00:32:51.175 --> 00:32:53.802
Therefore. she had
a reasonable expectation

779
00:32:53.927 --> 00:32:55.512
of marital privilege.

780
00:32:55.554 --> 00:32:58.849
The concept of privilege
was designed to protect

781
00:32:58.891 --> 00:33:02.978
relationships that society
places a special value on.

782
00:33:03.020 --> 00:33:05.522
to promote candor
in those relationships.

783
00:33:05.564 --> 00:33:08.442
It dates back to common law.
and we're talking about

784
00:33:08.525 --> 00:33:10.027
extending it to a machine?

785
00:33:10.068 --> 00:33:11.130
Where does this end?

786
00:33:11.155 --> 00:33:13.115
I don't know. Mr. Price.

787
00:33:13.447 --> 00:33:16.366
and I think that's the point.

788
00:33:16.492 --> 00:33:19.369
The genius of the law
does not rest in a world

789
00:33:19.453 --> 00:33:22.164
that's dead and gone.

790
00:33:22.289 --> 00:33:25.375
But in its adaptability to
a world that is ever-changing.

791
00:33:25.417 --> 00:33:27.294
State versus Hunt.

792
00:33:27.319 --> 00:33:30.147
Five years ago. the prosecution
wins this debate.

793
00:33:30.172 --> 00:33:34.092
But now. in 2026. I believe
the spirit of marital privilege

794
00:33:34.259 --> 00:33:36.428
was alive in these conversations.

795
00:33:36.470 --> 00:33:38.347
They were meant to be private.

796
00:33:38.430 --> 00:33:41.517
They'll stay that way today.

797
00:33:41.642 --> 00:33:44.561
The jury is not going to see
Kate Leavy's communications

798
00:33:44.603 --> 00:33:46.438
with the grief bot.

799
00:33:46.522 --> 00:33:48.482
- None of it?
- None of it.

800
00:33:48.565 --> 00:33:52.736
Which dramatically hampers
our ability to argue motive.

801
00:33:52.778 --> 00:33:54.738
Unless we can turn up
new evidence on this thing

802
00:33:54.863 --> 00:33:57.324
before court resumes in the morning.

803
00:33:57.449 --> 00:34:00.202
meaningful evidence.

804
00:34:00.244 --> 00:34:02.579
we're gonna have to offer
Kate Leavy a deal.

805
00:34:02.663 --> 00:34:04.331
A plea?

806
00:34:04.356 --> 00:34:06.100
What are you talking. manslaughter here?

807
00:34:06.125 --> 00:34:07.960
What? Manslaughter?

808
00:34:08.043 --> 00:34:10.337
At this point.
we'd be lucky if she says yes.

809
00:34:10.420 --> 00:34:11.880
But we know she did this.

810
00:34:11.964 --> 00:34:14.633
She looked me straight in the eye
and confessed in detail.

811
00:34:14.758 --> 00:34:17.594
And the jury will never
know that either.

812
00:34:17.719 --> 00:34:19.221
You have till tomorrow morning.

813
00:34:28.188 --> 00:34:29.523
You know. I was really hoping

814
00:34:29.606 --> 00:34:32.818
to make the Ranger game tonight.

815
00:34:32.943 --> 00:34:34.987
Would manslaughter really be that bad?

816
00:34:35.070 --> 00:34:37.614
I just got off the phone
with the warden of Rikers.

817
00:34:37.698 --> 00:34:40.617
Turns out. every single day
since her arrest.

818
00:34:40.701 --> 00:34:42.578
Kate Leavy has signed up
to access the internet

819
00:34:42.703 --> 00:34:45.080
on DOC-issued tablets.

820
00:34:45.164 --> 00:34:47.124
And the only thing
she's interested in is...

821
00:34:47.149 --> 00:34:48.433
Talking to her dead husband.

822
00:34:48.458 --> 00:34:49.835
Bingo.

823
00:34:49.918 --> 00:34:52.963
But she can't. because
Memory Branch turned him off.

824
00:34:53.046 --> 00:34:54.381
That's the end of that. then.

825
00:34:54.423 --> 00:34:57.426
Unless we got him turned back on.

826
00:34:57.509 --> 00:35:01.054
What if we brought Brian Leavy
back from the dead

827
00:35:01.180 --> 00:35:02.764
one more time?

828
00:35:11.023 --> 00:35:13.108
Okay. I'll talk to him.

829
00:35:13.567 --> 00:35:14.902
[PHONE BEEPS]

830
00:35:15.027 --> 00:35:16.403
Hey.

831
00:35:16.445 --> 00:35:18.071
Just spoke with Detective Walker.

832
00:35:18.197 --> 00:35:19.323
Says they're on to something.

833
00:35:19.406 --> 00:35:20.866
[NOTIFICATION CHIMES]

834
00:35:23.076 --> 00:35:24.203
What is it?

835
00:35:24.328 --> 00:35:27.831
Apparently Kate Leavy is
pleading guilty to murder?

836
00:35:27.956 --> 00:35:29.792
What?

837
00:35:29.917 --> 00:35:32.377
- That doesn't make any sense.
- Yeah.

838
00:35:32.461 --> 00:35:35.214
Our case is falling apart.
and her lawyer knows that.

839
00:35:35.297 --> 00:35:36.632
She knows that.

840
00:35:39.786 --> 00:35:42.038
What the hell happened?

841
00:35:42.387 --> 00:35:44.014
Kate. I was wrong.

842
00:35:44.139 --> 00:35:45.891
I'm so sorry.

843
00:35:48.143 --> 00:35:50.187
There was no cover-up?

844
00:35:50.312 --> 00:35:51.897
No.

845
00:35:51.980 --> 00:35:54.441
No. there was nothing wrong
with that helicopter.

846
00:35:54.483 --> 00:35:59.002
It was pilot error.
my error. like the FAA said.

847
00:36:00.405 --> 00:36:02.825
That poor man. Mark Turner.

848
00:36:02.950 --> 00:36:04.701
he was just doing his job. honey.

849
00:36:04.827 --> 00:36:06.245
[TENSE MUSIC]

850
00:36:06.328 --> 00:36:09.665
I did this. not you.

851
00:36:09.748 --> 00:36:11.500
I love you. Brian.

852
00:36:11.625 --> 00:36:14.336
and nothing can ever change that.

853
00:36:16.505 --> 00:36:19.383
But the fact is.

854
00:36:19.424 --> 00:36:23.095
I killed a man for nothing.

855
00:36:24.763 --> 00:36:27.141
What the hell have you done?

856
00:36:27.224 --> 00:36:30.644
I helped Kate Leavy see
the error of her ways.

857
00:36:30.686 --> 00:36:33.355
What. am I supposed to be
apologizing right now?

858
00:36:33.480 --> 00:36:35.566
You went to the CEO of Memory Branch

859
00:36:35.649 --> 00:36:38.360
and persuaded her
to turn Brian Leavy back on.

860
00:36:38.485 --> 00:36:39.903
and you manipulated the algorithm

861
00:36:39.987 --> 00:36:41.905
by feeding it the FAA report?

862
00:36:41.947 --> 00:36:44.616
Yeah. and it worked.

863
00:36:44.658 --> 00:36:46.368
Not the point.

864
00:36:48.203 --> 00:36:49.663
We have no choice.

865
00:36:49.688 --> 00:36:51.107
We have to disclose
Detective Walker's actions

866
00:36:51.132 --> 00:36:53.134
- to the defense.
- Do we?

867
00:36:53.375 --> 00:36:55.169
Let's just take a look
at the fuse on this bomb

868
00:36:55.210 --> 00:36:57.421
before we light it. okay?

869
00:36:57.463 --> 00:37:00.883
Kate Leavy attempted to speak
with her dead husband

870
00:37:00.966 --> 00:37:03.177
every day since her arrest.

871
00:37:03.302 --> 00:37:04.761
Couldn't you argue that Detective Walker

872
00:37:04.845 --> 00:37:06.722
just gave her what she wanted?

873
00:37:06.805 --> 00:37:09.933
Or handed her the shovel
to dig her own grave.

874
00:37:10.058 --> 00:37:11.560
[SIGHS]

875
00:37:11.643 --> 00:37:14.980
Walker facilitated this without
her attorney's knowledge.

876
00:37:15.063 --> 00:37:17.232
It's essentially ex parte communication.

877
00:37:17.357 --> 00:37:18.692
Right.

878
00:37:18.775 --> 00:37:21.487
And he tampered
with the machine's algorithm.

879
00:37:21.570 --> 00:37:24.281
He fed the thing new information

880
00:37:24.323 --> 00:37:28.660
with the express intent or hope
of soliciting a new confession.

881
00:37:28.702 --> 00:37:31.121
Which you have to applaud on some level.

882
00:37:31.163 --> 00:37:32.706
I'm not so sure about that.

883
00:37:32.790 --> 00:37:35.584
Detective Walker had no way of knowing

884
00:37:35.667 --> 00:37:37.753
that Kate Leavy was going to
initiate communication

885
00:37:37.836 --> 00:37:39.379
with this grief bot.

886
00:37:39.421 --> 00:37:40.923
He merely made the thing
available to her.

887
00:37:41.006 --> 00:37:42.925
Nick. come on.

888
00:37:43.050 --> 00:37:46.094
I don't like this
any more than you do. but...

889
00:37:46.178 --> 00:37:47.888
The high road is a lonely place.

890
00:37:50.015 --> 00:37:51.934
Notify the defense.

891
00:37:54.144 --> 00:37:55.521
This information warrants

892
00:37:55.562 --> 00:37:57.314
an immediate dismissal of charges.

893
00:37:57.397 --> 00:37:59.483
Dismissal is extreme.

894
00:37:59.508 --> 00:38:01.835
but there is no clear
constitutional violation.

895
00:38:01.860 --> 00:38:04.530
Mr. Price. give her the floor. please.

896
00:38:04.613 --> 00:38:07.241
Given what's happened here.
it's clearly her serve.

897
00:38:07.366 --> 00:38:11.119
Your Honor. this calls for a mistrial.

898
00:38:11.245 --> 00:38:13.455
The Sixth Amendment.
not to mention Massiah.

899
00:38:13.539 --> 00:38:16.333
tells us that the police
cannot deliberately prompt

900
00:38:16.458 --> 00:38:19.253
a represented defendant
to incriminate herself

901
00:38:19.336 --> 00:38:20.754
without her lawyer present.

902
00:38:20.838 --> 00:38:22.422
- That is not what happened.
- Of course it is.

903
00:38:22.548 --> 00:38:25.217
This grief bot is still a private app.

904
00:38:25.300 --> 00:38:27.136
It's not like
Detective Walker controlled it

905
00:38:27.219 --> 00:38:28.762
with some magical joystick.

906
00:38:28.787 --> 00:38:30.205
He turned the damn thing
into an agent of the state.

907
00:38:30.230 --> 00:38:31.815
The connection is too indirect

908
00:38:31.840 --> 00:38:33.117
to be a Massiah violation.

909
00:38:33.142 --> 00:38:34.476
Stop.

910
00:38:34.501 --> 00:38:36.036
Stop. stop.

911
00:38:36.061 --> 00:38:37.938
Just please stop.

912
00:38:38.021 --> 00:38:40.566
My husband has shown me
the error of my ways.

913
00:38:40.649 --> 00:38:43.068
I killed an innocent man.

914
00:38:43.152 --> 00:38:45.612
[TENSE MUSIC]

915
00:38:45.737 --> 00:38:48.365
I must take responsibility.

916
00:38:48.407 --> 00:38:52.161
Kate. don't do this.

917
00:38:52.244 --> 00:38:54.121
Ms. Leavy. it's not
my place to weigh in here.

918
00:38:54.146 --> 00:38:56.108
but you should listen to your attorney.

919
00:38:57.458 --> 00:39:00.502
Your husband is dead.
You weren't talking to him.

920
00:39:00.586 --> 00:39:02.629
It doesn't matter.

921
00:39:02.713 --> 00:39:04.131
I...

922
00:39:06.550 --> 00:39:11.217
I felt like I was.

923
00:39:11.930 --> 00:39:15.017
That was enough.

924
00:39:15.142 --> 00:39:18.061
I must atone.

925
00:39:18.145 --> 00:39:19.521
This is the only way.

926
00:39:21.482 --> 00:39:26.236
Ms. Leavy. did you kill Mark Turner?

927
00:39:26.320 --> 00:39:27.488
Yes. I did.

928
00:39:27.613 --> 00:39:29.198
Are you guilty of murder?

929
00:39:29.323 --> 00:39:32.350
♪ ♪

930
00:39:36.330 --> 00:39:37.998
Yes.

931
00:39:42.669 --> 00:39:44.838
I am.

932
00:39:50.886 --> 00:39:54.890
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

933
00:39:59.295 --> 00:40:02.915
Remind me never to subscribe
to a grief bot.

934
00:40:02.940 --> 00:40:05.901
First it convinces Kate Leavy
to commit murder.

935
00:40:05.984 --> 00:40:09.279
Then it gives her the worst
legal advice in history.

936
00:40:09.363 --> 00:40:10.823
[SIGHS]

937
00:40:10.906 --> 00:40:12.574
Well. I'm gonna go read a book.

938
00:40:12.658 --> 00:40:14.243
[CHUCKLES]

939
00:40:21.708 --> 00:40:24.586
[SOFT MUSIC]

940
00:40:24.711 --> 00:40:30.634
♪ ♪

941
00:40:30.717 --> 00:40:32.094
Hi. Nolan.

942
00:40:32.136 --> 00:40:33.762
It's Dad.

943
00:40:33.846 --> 00:40:36.598
Ah. jeez.

944
00:40:36.682 --> 00:40:39.726
I guess with these damn
computers in our pocket.

945
00:40:39.768 --> 00:40:42.437
I don't really have to say
who it is. do I?

946
00:40:42.521 --> 00:40:44.106
[CHUCKLES]

947
00:40:44.231 --> 00:40:49.027
Anyway. I... I just called
to hear your voice

948
00:40:49.111 --> 00:40:52.322
and really to tell you

949
00:40:52.406 --> 00:40:55.200
how proud I am. son.

950
00:40:55.325 --> 00:41:00.164
Well. when you get a chance.
give the old man a call.

951
00:41:00.205 --> 00:41:01.665
Love you. son.

952
00:41:01.748 --> 00:41:03.000
Bye.

953
00:41:03.083 --> 00:41:05.428
♪ ♪

954
